FBIS3-50598 "drlat003_i_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 Nicaragua Sandinists To Hold First Special Congress on 20 May PA0401131894 Managua BARRICADA in Spanish 2 Jan 94 pp 7, 8 PA0401131894 Managua BARRICADA Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Darwin Juarez] [Excerpt] The First Special Congress of the Sandinist National Liberation Front [FSLN] will be held on 20 May 1994. The agenda includes issues that are essential to the existence of the FSLN and points in three directions: reform of the statutes, reform of the program, and election of authorities. Prior to the congress and starting in January 1994, the organizing commission -- headed by FSLN founder Tomas Borge Martinez -- will make an intense effort in all the country's departments to ensure the participation of the Sandinist delegates and members in the preparatory debates. [passage omitted]
